[
  "Paradise is the CEO of mobile gaming company Skillz, which he cofounded with Casey Chafkin in 2012. ",
  "Skillz became the first publicly-traded mobile e-sports platform after a SPAC merger in December 2020. Paradise owns 22% of the company.",
  "Skillz had 2.6 million monthly active users in 2020, and 13% of them were paying customers generating $230 million in revenue for the year.",
  "Users can pay small entry fees to compete against others for cash prizes in games including bingo and variations of solitaire and blackjack.",
  "Prior to Skillz, Paradise sold his mobile payments company AisleBuyer to Intuit in 2012 for a reported price of $80 million to $100 million."
]